<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4044] [performance]decrease IO calls when flush hlog</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4044</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;    We found that the hlog flush to disk would block other write threads. When one thread exec &quot;doWrite(info, logKey, edit);&quot;, the others wait for &quot;updateLock&quot; in HLog.java.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Why not the others add their edits into a list and wait. When sync&apos;s time, the whole list sync to disk once. I think it will decrease the IO calls. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    So Maybe we will make two lists for edits. Each thread write to the &quot;waledits&quot; and wait for &quot;updateLock&quot;. Each thread can copy the &quot;waledits&quot; to &quot;flushedits&quot; and flush the &quot;flushedits&quot; to disk once it gets &quot;updateLock&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    In my test, it can increase the write speed of 100% when I set &quot;hbase.regionserver.handler.count&quot;=100.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
